        // ── Accounts & Bulk-Assign (Article) ─────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Accounts & Bulk-Assigning Leads",
            Slug = "leads-accounts",
            Summary = "B2B Accounts group multiple contacts under one parent company; how to create accounts, link leads to them, and bulk-assign many leads at once.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 4,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 9,
            AppRoutes = """["/leads/accounts","/leads"]""",
            Tags = """["leads","accounts","b2b"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Accounts & Bulk-Assigning Leads\n\n**Accounts** are multi-contact B2B parent groupings. When one prospect company has several people you're working — an engineer, a procurement contact, an executive sponsor — a single Lead row would force you to pick which contact to surface. An Account lets all of those leads roll up under one company umbrella instead.\n\nFind accounts at **Leads → Accounts**.\n\n### What an Account Holds\n\nAn account describes the parent company:\n\n- **Account name** (required), **Industry**, **Size bracket**.\n- **Address** — city, state, postal code, country.\n- **Website**, **Phone**, **Description**.\n\nThe accounts list table shows Name, Industry, Size, City, State, a **Contacts** count, a **Leads** count (how many leads point at this account), and the created date.\n\n### Creating an Account\n\nClick **New Account** in the toolbar, fill in the name (required) and any company details, and save. You can also create an account right from the New Lead panel's account picker — click **New Account** there to add one without leaving the lead you're creating.\n\n### Linking a Lead to an Account\n\nThere are two ways a lead gets tied to an account:\n\n1. **At intake** — the New Lead panel has an account picker. Pick an existing account, or create one on the spot.\n2. **In bulk** — from the main Leads list, select multiple leads and assign them to an account in one action (below).\n\nWhen a linked lead is later converted to a Customer, the account's contacts roll forward as non-primary contacts on the resulting Customer record, so the relationship survives conversion.\n\n### Bulk-Assigning Leads to an Account\n\nOn the main **Leads** list (table view), each row has a checkbox. Select one or more leads and a **bulk action bar** appears at the top of the table showing how many are selected. Click **Assign Account**, pick the target account (you can create a new one here too), and confirm. Every selected lead is linked to that account in one step.\n\nThis is the fast way to organize a pile of freshly imported leads — select the ones that belong to the same parent company and assign them together.\n\n### Deleting an Account\n\nYou **can't delete** an account while any lead is still linked to it — you'll get a message telling you how many leads are linked. Unassign the account on those leads first, then try again. Already-converted leads aren't affected by deleting an account.","sections":[]}"""
