        // ── Sample Shipment Tracking (Article) ───────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Sample Shipment Tracking",
            Slug = "leads-samples",
            Summary = "The cross-lead view of pre-quote sample parts: the sample lifecycle, status filtering, advancing samples, and recording outcomes.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 4,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 10,
            AppRoutes = """["/leads/samples"]""",
            Tags = """["leads","samples","presales"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Sample Shipment Tracking\n\nBefore a quote is firm, you often send a prospect a **sample part** to evaluate. The Sample Shipments page (Leads → Samples) is the cross-lead read view of every sample in flight — so sales managers can spot stale samples (delivered but no follow-up quote) and reps can see where each prospect sits in the sample-evaluation loop.\n\n### What the List Shows\n\nThe table lists every sample across all leads, with columns for the **Lead** it belongs to, **Part** description, **Quantity**, **Status**, the **Requested / Shipped / Delivered** dates, **Cost** to us, and the **Tracking** number (carrier + tracking). Clicking a row opens that sample's lead detail.\n\n### The Sample Lifecycle\n\nA sample moves through a linear lifecycle, then ends in one of three outcomes:\n\n1. **Requested** — a sample has been asked for.\n2. **Approved** — the request is approved to send.\n3. **Shipped** — the sample is on its way (a ship date is stamped).\n4. **Delivered** — the prospect has it (a delivery date is stamped).\n\nThen an outcome:\n\n- **Quoted** (Quoted from sample) — the sample led to a quote. Success.\n- **Lost** (Lost from sample) — the sample didn't convert.\n- **Stale** — delivered but went quiet with no follow-up.\n\n### Advancing a Sample\n\nThe linear steps move forward one at a time. On each row, an **advance arrow** moves the sample to its next status — Requested → Approved → Shipped → Delivered. Advancing to Shipped or Delivered stamps the matching date automatically. Once a sample reaches Delivered (or an outcome), there's no further advance arrow.\n\n### Recording an Outcome\n\nRecording an outcome is a deliberate call you make, so it lives behind the row's **outcome menu** (the three-dot button) rather than the advance arrow:\n\n- **Mark Quoted from sample** — the sample produced a quote.\n- **Mark Lost from sample** — it didn't convert.\n- **Mark Stale** — manually flag it as gone cold.\n\nNote that **Stale** is also set for you automatically once a delivered sample goes quiet for a while with no follow-up quote, so you usually don't have to mark it by hand.\n\n### Filtering\n\nThe status filter at the top narrows the list. Beyond filtering to a single status, two convenience options help:\n\n- **All** — every sample.\n- **Open (not yet outcome)** — everything still in the active lifecycle (Requested through Delivered), hiding the Quoted / Lost / Stale outcomes. This is the view managers use to see what's genuinely in flight.\n\n### Where Samples Are Created\n\nThis page is read-and-manage-status only. Reps **request a sample from the lead's detail panel**, where the sample lives functionally. This cross-lead page is for tracking and moving samples through their lifecycle, not creating them.","sections":[]}"""
